The paper presents a visual-inertial odometry algorithm for Micro Aerial Vehicles (MAVs), which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm uses a downward facing camera, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of a joint cost function, which could involve machine learning or optimization techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm in various scenarios, which could involve control systems or system identification (cs.SY).
